Date: Thu, 17 Nov 2011 08:52:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 16/22] powerpc/85xx: add eLBC error interrupt in dts for
 P3041

On P3041, eLBC error interrupts are routed to 0(ORed Error Interrupt),
eLBC event interrupts are routed to 9(ELBC), so add the error interrupt
in dts for P3041.

Signed-off-by: Shaohui Xie <Shaohui.Xie@freescale.com>
Signed-off-by: Kumar Gala <galak@kernel.crashing.org>

[Extracted from FSL QorIQ-SDK-V1.2-SOURCE-20120614-yocto.iso image]
Signed-off-by:Jiang Lu <lu.jiang@windriver.com>
[Rebase on sdkv1.3 context.]
Signed-off-by: Tiejun Chen <tiejun.chen@windriver.com>
---
 arch/powerpc/boot/dts/fsl/p3041si-post.dtsi |    7 +++++--
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/fsl/p3041si-post.dtsi b/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/fsl/p3041si-post.dtsi
index f6baf4a..ef23d55 100644
--- a/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/fsl/p3041si-post.dtsi
+++ b/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/fsl/p3041si-post.dtsi
@@ -33,8 +33,11 @@
  */
 
 &lbc {
-	compatible = "fsl,p3041-elbc", "fsl,elbc", "simple-bus";
-	interrupts = <25 2 0 0>;
+	compatible = "fsl,p3041-rev1.0-elbc", "simple-bus";
+	interrupts = <
+		25 2 0 0
+		16 2 1 19
+		>;
 	#address-cells = <2>;
 	#size-cells = <1>;
 };
